The paper deals with autonomous mapping and exploration for range sensing mobile robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Gaussian Processes (GPs) for occupancy mapping and exploration is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of gradient-based methods for computing probabilistic frontier maps, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the control and decision-making aspects of the robot, which falls under the field of systems and control (cs.SY).
